  

<h5 id="pierce-index-reckless"><a href="https://ellanew.com/2025/10/06/inktober-pierce" title="wikilink"><span class="small-caps">⬅️</span> <span class="small-caps">PIERCE</span></a> · <a href="https://ellanew.com/2025/10/01/inktober-index" title="wikilink"><span class="small-caps">INDEX</span></a> · <a href="https://ellanew.com/2025/10/08/inktober-reckless" title="wikilink"><span class="small-caps">RECKLESS</span> <span class="small-caps">➡️</span></a></h5>
<p><img src="https://cdn.blot.im/blog_177bc256f0ee469c998e912e20ece048/_image_cache/eae62c8f-4225-4efc-9140-eda71f14b4fd.png" alt="Ink drawing of a small human in a starfish suit, surrounded by stars and tiny fish" width="1273" height="1076"></p>
<p><em>Ink on paper, drawn with non-dominant hand</em></p>
<hr>
<p>Last year I started crocheting a <a href="https://www.etsy.com/au/listing/1692901294/pdf-pattern-juni-starsuit-for-newborn-0" target="_blank">starfish suit</a> for my 6th grandchild. The yarn was difficult to work with and the sizing wasn’t working out, so I stuffed the project into a bag where it remains to this day. Soon (I tell myself) I shall either complete it, recycle it, or set it free some other way.</p>
<hr>
<p><img src="https://cdn.blot.im/blog_177bc256f0ee469c998e912e20ece048/_image_cache/ddc78c24-3946-46ba-9ac3-32f35e6b3100.png" alt="Underwater scene drawn with coloured textas. There is a sun in the top left corner, and we can see the waves near the top of the picture. Many starfish of varying sizes are floating around under the water" width="1272" height="1698"> <em>Artist: S</em></p>
